When occupants need to pass through another room or space to access the required exit, the following conditions must be complied with:
(1) the exit access door separating the rooms or spaces must only be fitted with an electromechanical device designed in accordance with  2.3.9k.(2);
(2) the doorway of the exit access door must not be blocked/obstructed and must be kept clear at all times;
(3) warning signs with the wording 'Exit Access Door - Keep Clear' must be placed prominently on both sides of the exit access door; and
(4) the egress paths through the exit access door must be suitably demarcated.
